instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "Control commands are issued by the Digital Twin to the Raspberry Pi controller via RabbitMQ. The controller receives the messages, interprets them as actuator commands (e.g., turn the heatbed or fan on/off), and forwards the commands to the low‑level driver, which then drives the MOSFET‑based power stage and optocouplers to actuate the heatbed and fan. The low‑level driver validates each command against a safe protocol before execution. Feedback on actuator state is published back to RabbitMQ so that the Digital Twin can confirm execution."
]

